Class EnumerableMapResolver

java.lang.Object

      org.forgerock.openig.resolver.EnumerableMapResolver
All Implemented Interfaces:
Resolver, Indexed<Class>
public class EnumerableMapResolver
extends ReadableMapResolver

Resolves EnumerableMap objects. This implementation uses duck-typing to attempt access to the object. It will successfully resolve the object if it exposes the methods defined in the EnumerableMap interface.

getKey

public Class getKey()
Description copied from interface: Resolver
Returns the type of object that the resolver supports. This does not necessarily guarantee that the resolver will provide resolution; rather this is how a resolver specifies what type of object it may resolve. Resolvers for more specific classes and interfaces are called earlier than those of more general classes and interfaces.

containsKey

public boolean containsKey(Object object,
                           Object element)
Description copied from interface: Resolver
Returns true if the object contains the specified element. The object argument references an object for which a named or indexed element is being sought. The element argument specifies which element is being sought.

The element argument can be either a String or an Integer object. A string represents a named element of an associative array; an integer represents the index of an ordered array.

If the resolver cannot resolve the requested element, then false should be returned. This allows other resovlers of more generic classes or interfaces to potentially resolve the requested element.
